Flames shot from Thassalin's maw as the huge Thraki set a specific piece of forest in motion and then circled overhead to detect any movements. Strangely, the eerie screeching behind him ceased as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
"What's going on, Tenuk, you already turned yourself into a Thraki once!"
"If I fly myself, it's completely different from being suddenly lifted up by a huge pink dragon!"
"So bad was it really, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not Nyssis opinion. He looked less black than usual, and his claws had dug so deeply into Thassalin's back that the Thraki was bleeding. However, it seemed to make no difference to Thassalin. Nevertheless, he had become aware that he had frightened his new friends, and landed on a clearing.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I SMELLED SOMETHING. I HAD TO TAKE CARE OF IT!"
" But did you have to drag us along?," growled Tenuk as he climbed down from Thassalin's back and slid down onto his tail. "And we left Retvik behind! Our big, strong fighter was left behind! How is he supposed to catch up with us?"
"HE'LL THINK OF SOMETHING…," GROWLED NYSSI. "RETVIK ISN'T THE FASTEST, BUT HE'S NOT STUPID."
"YES, BUT CAN RETVIK DRIVE?"
Nyssi winked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he can drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik drive a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I haven't seen him drive a nice little car like Kayel's either. Besides, he only started using the car for work because you always drive us. He only has his bicycle."
Roaring laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly seemed to find something utterly ridiculous, but no one knew what he was laughing about. It took a little too long for Thassalin to calm down.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR HUGE FRIEND IN ARMOR ON SUCH A TINY SMALL BIKE FOR TEMTHAN-KIDS. THAT WAS JUST PURELY LAUGHABLE! I WISH I HAD SOME KIND OF TELEPATHY. A BEAUTIFUL IMAGINATION! ONE I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel chuckled, as he could guess what was going on in Thassalin's mind. "Yes, that's true. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly take off so abruptly?"
Thassalin grunted, took off and disappeared. When he returned after a short time, he threw a lifeless creature at Nyssi's feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, pale gold dragon-like being. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEAD ONE. I HEAR THEIR SCREECHES. I SMELL THEIR BLOOD. SOMETHING DRIVES ME TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI COMMANDS. THEY ARE VERY CLOSE."
The mighty Thraki froze suddenly. Nyssi and Kayel froze as well, watching intently at a gap in the clearing. Something large and black stared at them and growled. Whatever it was, it spread two massive wings and shot toward Thassalin, ignoring the three smaller beings between them. Kayel and Tenuk barely managed to take cover, but Nyssi was dragged along and nearly flung onto Thassalin.
Thassalin responded to the attack by grabbing Nyssi and flinging him onto his back with his incredibly long and dexterous tail before taking to the air himself. The black, double-winged creature pursued them at high speed.
Kayel snapped in annoyance while taking his rifle off his back and opening a pouch that contained a belt of ammunition. He slung the belt over his chest, but quickly noticed that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were out of sight.
"Hey, Tenuk, could you turn into something that can fly?" asked Kayel.
"Would you like to follow them?"
"Of course!"
"but... one of them is a huge monster!"
"Of course! I'm standing here with a top-notch rifle in my hand and could shoot at them right now. But, well, you know— I'd have to see them first in order to hit them."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to make more room. With a soft, pained grunt, his body stretched out, his fur turned into scales and his arms into wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, light-blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Like a normal Thraki, Tenuk now had a decent scale shield running along his back. Practically, he also had a pair of spines growing on his back, which Kayel could hold on to. It took a little too long for Tenuk to get the takeoff going, but once in the air, he oriented himself quickly and tried to take up the pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature shot up beneath them, and Tenuk barely avoided a collision.
"Is that the other terrifying giant monster Lanex was afraid of?" Kayel frowned. He tried to shoot at the second beast, missed, and hastily reloaded.
Tenuk said nothing. He was too focused on flying toward Nyssi and Thassalin, even though the other creature was pursuing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to keep the monster in sight. For Kayel, the fact that it was following them was an advantage, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots went through the upper wings of the creature. It screamed in pain and sank back under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but it would certainly not be able to keep up with them.
A short distance ahead, Nyssi clung desperately as Thassalin swung around and spat fire at the charred monster. The creature was definitely injured. It seemed furious but not ready to give up. The fireballs weren't having the desired effect. As Thassalin stretched out, Nyssi seized the opportunity to draw her own weapon, an old-fashioned shot gun. It wasn't necessarily the first choice, but maybe the shot would scare off the black beast.
